Note: Sample 15 - String Interpolation & Inline Comments

Let name be "Alice".
Let age be 30.

--- This is an inline comment using triple dashes
Say "Hello, {name}! You are {age} years old.".

Let x be 10.
Let y be 20.
// This is a C-style inline comment
Say "The sum of {x} and {y} is {x plus y}.".

Say "Escaped braces: use \{ and \} to show literal braces.".

Let greeting be "Welcome to Plain Language v6, {name}!".
Say greeting.
